97
00:07:54,619 --> 00:07:58,800
 Jingjing, if you're getting married, what kind of wedding do you want? 

98
00:08:01,560 --> 00:08:07,020
 My dream wedding should be a very, very romantic one. 

99
00:08:07,020 --> 00:08:11,299
 I'll have the ground littered with flowers, invite lots and lots of friends, 

100
00:08:11,299 --> 00:08:12,900
 and we'll all sing and dance together. 

101
00:08:12,900 --> 00:08:15,879
 I'll wear a white wedding dress, and gradually walk towards the groom, 

102
00:08:15,879 --> 00:08:18,180
 Then he'll hold my hand and put a ring on me, 

103
00:08:18,180 --> 00:08:20,759
 and we'll recite our vows. 

104
00:08:20,759 --> 00:08:24,079
 To me, that's love at its best. 

105
00:08:28,639 --> 00:08:31,539
 If there are stars in the sky, then it should be quite romantic. 

106
00:08:31,539 --> 00:08:34,559
 This is my very ideal romantic wedding. 

107
00:08:40,020 --> 00:08:42,740
   

108
00:08:44,358 --> 00:08:45,637
 Who's there? 

109
00:08:45,639 --> 00:08:47,139
It's me.

110
00:08:48,840 --> 00:08:50,179
What brought you here?

111
00:08:50,179 --> 00:08:51,679
Tomorrow is the weekend?

112
00:08:51,679 --> 00:08:54,320
Come in quick.

113
00:08:54,320 --> 00:08:55,920
Come on.

114
00:09:01,699 --> 00:09:04,210
Why do we have to attend a group wedding?

115
00:09:07,860 --> 00:09:11,459
Did you drive over 200 kilometers just to ask me this question?

116
00:09:11,459 --> 00:09:12,900
You said it.

117
00:09:12,900 --> 00:09:16,159
You've dreamed of a very romantic wedding littered with flowers.

118
00:09:16,159 --> 00:09:17,380
And lots and lots of friends will be invited.

119
00:09:17,380 --> 00:09:20,659
Wait. When did I say that?

120
00:09:20,659 --> 00:09:22,159
Two years ago.

121
00:09:22,159 --> 00:09:24,510
When you were interviewed as a jewelry spokeswoman.

122
00:09:26,939 --> 00:09:29,120
Did you believe it?

123
00:09:29,120 --> 00:09:33,520
When they asked me during the interview, I had to make up an answer on the spot.

124
00:09:36,939 --> 00:09:39,320
Then what kind of wedding do you want?

125
00:09:44,939 --> 00:09:49,679
Yu Tu, do you think that I'm concerned about your finances,

126
00:09:49,679 --> 00:09:52,360
so I came up with the group wedding?

127
00:09:55,220 --> 00:09:57,000
Jingjing.

128
00:09:58,179 --> 00:10:00,670
I also want to do the best I can.

129
00:10:09,539 --> 00:10:11,839
Thank you.

130
00:10:11,839 --> 00:10:13,660
I'm about to marry you.

131
00:10:13,660 --> 00:10:16,370
Of course, you have to do your best.

132
00:10:16,377 --> 00:10:20,959
But this time, all I really need is just a simple wedding.

133
00:10:20,959 --> 00:10:24,820
You know that I'm at the center of attention.

134
00:10:24,820 --> 00:10:27,699
You must consider many things if you want to get married.

135
00:10:27,699 --> 00:10:31,598
You want to keep it secret, but it's hard to get it done.

136
00:10:31,600 --> 00:10:34,450
I want to invite only a few close friends.

137
00:10:35,079 --> 00:10:37,879
But someone will resent it.

138
00:10:37,879 --> 00:10:41,677
So in the end, our wedding may be a social gathering.

139
00:10:41,679 --> 00:10:46,059
We have to keep socializing, toasting, and taking photos.

140
00:10:46,059 --> 00:10:49,979
There may be a tiny hitch that might end up trending.

141
00:10:49,979 --> 00:10:54,299
But if we participate in your unit's wedding, such problems will no longer exist.

142
00:10:54,299 --> 00:10:57,479
By then, we'll simply be a pair of newlyweds,

143
00:10:57,479 --> 00:11:00,599
albeit with many more newlyweds. So what?

144
00:11:00,599 --> 00:11:03,420
There're so many people getting married every day.

145
00:11:03,420 --> 00:11:06,930
We are just an ordinary couple amongst them all.

146
00:11:07,781 --> 00:11:10,139
A young couple.

147
00:11:10,139 --> 00:11:12,939
But I think that belongs to both of us.

148
00:11:12,939 --> 00:11:18,190
Just you and I. No disturbance. No social media.

149
00:11:23,280 --> 00:11:25,299
A wedding is between two people.

150
00:11:25,299 --> 00:11:29,090
From you to me, and from me to you.

151
00:11:32,179 --> 00:11:36,030
I hope you don't mind having such a wedding.

152
00:11:54,100 --> 00:11:56,020
Jingjing.

153
00:11:57,220 --> 00:12:01,410
I suddenly felt that my previous proposal wasn't very formal.

154
00:12:02,480 --> 00:12:04,450
It was a bit rash.

155
00:12:10,360 --> 00:12:14,020
I want to do it again. To propose to you formally.

156
00:12:15,459 --> 00:12:19,540
I didn't think so, but... All right.

157
00:12:28,500 --> 00:12:30,660
Student Qiao Jingjing.

158
00:12:32,759 --> 00:12:35,350
We have known each other for almost 16 years.

159
00:12:35,986 --> 00:12:41,030
Because of my prejudices, we missed each other for thirteen years.

160
00:12:42,699 --> 00:12:45,070
You may not regret it,

161
00:12:45,720 --> 00:12:47,950
but I do.

162
00:12:49,519 --> 00:12:52,770
Fortunately, we still have decades ahead of us.

163
00:12:53,799 --> 00:12:57,240
Please leave the rest of your time to me.

164
00:13:01,039 --> 00:13:06,320
With diligence, and my best effort,

165
00:13:07,659 --> 00:13:09,950
I will be a good husband.

166
00:13:13,280 --> 00:13:17,283
Good. I will be good too.

167
00:13:26,620 --> 00:13:28,390
Thank you.

168
00:14:24,779 --> 00:14:26,510
Come in.

169
00:14:27,179 --> 00:14:28,880
Ms. Wang?

170
00:14:29,779 --> 00:14:33,320
Dr. Yu, what brings you here?

171
00:14:33,320 --> 00:14:37,260
Ms. Wang, I'm here to sign up for the group wedding.

172
00:14:41,700 --> 00:14:43,320
Dr. Yu.

173
00:14:44,480 --> 00:14:49,180
Well... do you have a new girlfriend?

174
00:14:53,579 --> 00:14:55,280
No.

175
00:15:08,860 --> 00:15:10,620
Here's the form.

176
00:15:12,579 --> 00:15:14,130
And a pen?

177
00:15:14,779 --> 00:15:16,440
Thanks.

178
00:15:32,659 --> 00:15:36,760
 Yu Tu, come to my office. 

179
00:15:39,092 --> 00:15:40,740
Professor.

180
00:15:40,740 --> 00:15:43,550
Yu Tu, come on in.

181
00:15:46,100 --> 00:15:47,730
Take a seat.

182
00:15:52,070 --> 00:15:54,290
Well...

183
00:15:56,059 --> 00:15:57,819
Have you...

184
00:15:57,819 --> 00:15:59,530
No.

185
00:16:00,219 --> 00:16:01,620
What?

186
00:16:01,620 --> 00:16:03,570
I don't have a new girlfriend.

187
00:16:04,539 --> 00:16:07,320
I wasn't about to ask you about that! If you had a new one,

188
00:16:07,320 --> 00:16:10,700
would the folks at that department have called me about it?

189
00:16:13,120 --> 00:16:15,530
I was about to ask you.

190
00:16:16,260 --> 00:16:21,699
Do you have any trouble turning around your finances?

191
00:16:21,699 --> 00:16:25,320
If that troubles you, my wife and I can help.

192
00:16:25,320 --> 00:16:28,179
Thank you. But I'm doing fine.

193
00:16:28,179 --> 00:16:33,460
Jingjing and I, we just want to make the wedding a little simpler.

194
00:16:33,460 --> 00:16:35,120
Did she agree to that?

195
00:16:35,120 --> 00:16:37,560
She suggested it.

196
00:16:37,560 --> 00:16:40,400
"She suggested it"?

197
00:16:40,400 --> 00:16:44,400
She's been rather mischievous.

198
00:16:44,979 --> 00:16:47,980
However, she wants to keep things simple.

199
00:16:47,980 --> 00:16:51,277
She thinks she'd get away from the media if we hold it in the institute.

200
00:16:51,279 --> 00:16:53,080
I know, that can't be possible.

201
00:16:53,080 --> 00:16:57,200
So last night, we discussed that if it couldn't be kept secret,

202
00:16:57,200 --> 00:17:01,159
then it'd probably affect my colleagues.

203
00:17:01,159 --> 00:17:02,917
So we won't attend.

204
00:17:02,919 --> 00:17:05,919
That was what I told Ms. Wang just now.

205
00:17:05,919 --> 00:17:09,100
Keeping your nuptials a secret? That's not a problem.

206
00:17:09,100 --> 00:17:12,398
We are the best at keeping secrets.

207
00:17:12,400 --> 00:17:14,940
By then

208
00:17:14,940 --> 00:17:19,890
you'll show up after the wedding ceremony begins.

209
00:17:21,100 --> 00:17:25,559
But what if the secret was leaked midway?

210
00:17:25,559 --> 00:17:27,820
What would you do?

211
00:17:27,820 --> 00:17:29,900
 Surely the wedding won't be held in the institute. 

212
00:17:29,900 --> 00:17:33,060
 It should be in a nearby hotel, just like it's always been. 

213
00:17:33,060 --> 00:17:35,889
 So it may not be kept secret. 

214
00:17:35,889 --> 00:17:38,680
 So it's not in your unit then? 

215
00:17:38,680 --> 00:17:42,239
 If someone finds out, we'll just run away? 

216
00:17:42,239 --> 00:17:44,659
 See, that's the benefit of joining a group wedding. 

217
00:17:44,659 --> 00:17:48,020
 If we hold our own wedding, we can't run anywhere. 

218
00:17:49,060 --> 00:17:51,459
 Then I'll have to get myself a pair of sneakers. 

219
00:17:51,459 --> 00:17:53,680
 You, too. 

220
00:17:53,680 --> 00:17:55,870
 I'll just get us one pair. 

221
00:17:57,380 --> 00:17:59,620
 You'll carry me on your back? 

222
00:17:59,620 --> 00:18:03,980
 Then I'll have to order a 50kg wedding dress. 

223
00:18:07,499 --> 00:18:10,830
 Can you cut it down to half? Make it 25 kg. 

224
00:18:12,300 --> 00:18:13,720
 12.5 kg? 

225
00:18:13,720 --> 00:18:16,172
 Plus me, that makes 100 kg! 

226
00:18:16,172 --> 00:18:18,120
 I need to eat more. 

227
00:18:21,019 --> 00:18:23,417
It depends on when it gets leaked.

228
00:18:23,417 --> 00:18:27,360
If it's early, we'll change plans.

229
00:18:27,360 --> 00:18:31,940
If the leak happens during the wedding...

230
00:18:34,739 --> 00:18:36,800
We'll flee right away.

231
00:18:36,800 --> 00:18:38,680
Once you're done hosting,

232
00:18:38,680 --> 00:18:41,419
find another place to host for us a second time.

233
00:18:41,419 --> 00:18:42,699
Are you kidding?

234
00:18:42,699 --> 00:18:44,820
This is a wedding, not a guerrilla gig!

235
00:18:44,820 --> 00:18:47,340
This is simply nonsensical.

236
00:18:48,259 --> 00:18:51,518
Professor. Have some water.

237
00:18:56,540 --> 00:18:58,420
You're so sly.

238
00:18:58,420 --> 00:19:01,320
Are you setting me up?

239
00:19:04,400 --> 00:19:09,800
Yu Tu. At last, you've completed the most important event of your life.

240
00:19:09,800 --> 00:19:12,060
I'm so happy for you.

241
00:19:13,219 --> 00:19:15,858
Xiao Qiao is a fine young lady.

242
00:19:15,858 --> 00:19:20,100
From now on, you must treat her well.

243
00:19:22,160 --> 00:19:23,660
I will.

244
00:19:25,540 --> 00:19:28,060
   

245
00:19:31,620 --> 00:19:33,659
   

246
00:19:33,659 --> 00:19:35,939
    
 Families to the air show, get on the bus here.

247
00:19:35,939 --> 00:19:38,459
We're about to set off soon.

248
00:19:52,340 --> 00:19:53,979
Are they here already?

249
00:19:53,979 --> 00:19:55,880
The bride is still wearing a veil.

250
00:19:55,880 --> 00:19:57,839
No one seemed to notice them.

251
00:19:57,839 --> 00:19:59,879
Let's leave them alone.

252
00:20:01,979 --> 00:20:05,299
Why are there some brides who haven't put on their makeup?

253
00:20:09,540 --> 00:20:11,480
Fix this for me.

254
00:20:15,340 --> 00:20:17,859
- There you go. 
 - Okay.

255
00:20:20,559 --> 00:20:22,177
There are so many people.

256
00:20:22,177 --> 00:20:23,720
Are you nervous?

257
00:20:23,720 --> 00:20:25,060
